<?php $__env->startSection('content'); ?><p>Junior MasterChef is coming soon to Channel Ten. </p>

<p>And it appears the young cooks appearing on the show are just as impressive as the grown up contestants. </p>

<p>In a preview which aired on Monday night, and was shared to the show's social media accounts, the budding chefs wowed the judges with incredible creations. </p>

<p>Impressed! Junior MasterChef is coming soon to Channel Ten. MasterChef Australia judges Jock Zonfrillo (left), Melissa Leong (centre) and Andy Allen (right) all return to the MasterChef kitchen to host the show </p>

<p>MasterChef Australia judges Jock Zonfrillo, Melissa Leong and Andy Allen all return to the MasterChef kitchen to host the show. </p>

<p>And in the clip, Jock is seen looking absolutely stunned after trying a dish made by one of the nine to 14 year old contestants.  </p>

<p>'What I tasted there was a passion I would expect from a cook that had been in the kitchen for 20 odd years,' he exclaimed. </p>

